actions.text: Referred to the House Committee on Financial Services.
Mr. McHenry moved to suspend the rules and pass the bill.
Considered under suspension of the rules.
DEBATE - The House proceeded with forty minutes of debate on H.R. 1097.
On motion to suspend the rules and pass the bill Agreed to by voice vote.
Motion to reconsider laid on the table Agreed to without objection.
Received in the Senate and Read twice and referred to the Committee on Banking, Housing, and Urban Affairs.
Senate Committee on Banking, Housing, and Urban Affairs discharged by Unanimous Consent.
Passed Senate without amendment by Unanimous Consent.
Message on Senate action sent to the House.

official_title: To award a Congressional Gold Medal to Everett Alvarez, Jr., in recognition of his service to the Nation.
short_title: Everett Alvarez, Jr. Congressional Gold Medal Act of 2023

summary.text:
Everett Alvarez, Jr. Congressional Gold Medal Act of 2023

This act provides for the award of a Congressional Gold Medal to Everett Alvarez Jr. in recognition of his service to the nation.
